<http://www.promedmail.org>
[see: National disease bulletins: survey 20000106093939]
Date: Sun 9 Jan 2000
From: ProMED-mail <promed@promedmail.org>

[We have received information about some animal & plant disease bulletins
which will be posted separately - Mod.JW]
WHO & CDC COUNTRY LINKS
---------------------------------------------
Date: 6 Jan 2000
From: "Marjorie P. Pollack" <pollackmp@mindspring.com>

The WHO website has a links page that is worth visiting:
http://www-nt.who.int/whosis/statistics/national_sites/national_sites.cfm
[It certainly is, & it has sites for dozens of countries -- but most of them
are not epidemiological bulletins, which are what ProMED-mail is interested
in. - Mod.JW]
For links to other sites, including USA state health departments, CDC has a
links page: http://www.cdc.gov/other.htm
[Another is http://www.cdc.gov/epo/mmwr/international/ with an index of many
national bulletins, including those in ex-Soviet countries. Unfortunately,
this has mostly not been updated since 1997 or early 1998. - Mod.JW]
