JAPAN
----------
Date: Fri, 07 Jan 2000 08:54:56 +0900
From: Narufumi Suganuma <suganuma@fmsrsa.fukui-med.ac.jp>

Please link to Infectious Disease Surveillance Center, National Institute
of Infectious Disease, Japan
http://idsc.nih.go.jp/index.html
This site deals with the national survey of infectious disease in Japan.
[In Japanese & English. Includes monthly IASR - Infectious Agents
Surveillance Reports, latest available December 1999, plus Isolation &
Detection Reports of Viruses and Bacteria, by Month, May 1998 - October
1999, and wonderful graphs of weekly & monthly trends over the last 10 years
for 21 infectious diseases - Mod.JW]
***
NETHERLANDS
----------------------
Date: Fri, 7 Jan 2000 14:35:14 +0100
From: Lynette Wijgergangs <Lynette.Wijgergangs@rivm.nl>

Our (monthly) Dutch National Bulletin on Communicable Diseases is available
(in Dutch with English abstracts) on:
http://www.isis.rivm.nl/inf_bul/home_bul.html

[Latest available issue is No.12, 1999. We were unable to find any English
abstracts - Mod.JW]
